Author:
Vol / Page: 17
Edition:
Quote: <i>shepherd v.</i> in N.Z., protect a rugby player illegally by coming between man and ball, and a would-be tackler; guard a mining claim and do little work on it, so as to preserve legal rights; whence shepherd, one who so holds a claim.
